<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.233.103096.figure51>
    dc:description "Figure 51. Uvariopsis bisexualis Verdc A flowering branch B flower bud, side view C sepal, outer view D flower, two petals removed, side view E detail of receptacle, some stamens fallen, side view F stamen, upper view G stamen, lower view H carpel, outer view J carpel, inner view K stigma L longitudinal section of carpel M transversal section of ovary. A-M from Lovett 233 (type). Drawings by Maureen Church, from Verdcourt (1986; fig. 3, p. 292), Kew Bulletin 1969 Royal Botanic Gardens, Kew." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/909910" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.3897/phytokeys.233.103096.figure52>
    dc:description "Figure 52. Distribution map of Uvariopsis bisexualis. Shades of grey represent elevation, from white (sea level) to darker grey (higher elevation). The inset shows the extent of the map over Africa." ;
